      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) features the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus for optimized torque delivery and timing. Mated to a precise G96 6-speed longitudinal manual transaxle, the drivetrain remains tight with consistent clutch take-up. The chassis architecture utilizes a multi-link rear suspension and MacPherson struts, maintaining excellent kinematic integrity. Braking is managed by four-piston aluminum monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, showing no signs of fade. While the aesthetic condition reflects honest road use, the mechanical vitals are robust; the IMS bearing and rear main seal have been addressed, and recent oil analysis confirms no significant particulate wear. A mechanically sound example for the enthusiast seeking a visceral, analog driving experience.",
